w.haberler.com/protokol-afyon-da-uretilen-celik-yelek-ve-3554794-haberi/|archive-date=24 September 2015|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=savar>{{cite web|title=Savar Kompozit|url=http://www.savarbalistik.com.tr/content.php?icerikpk=22|accessdate=5 April 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140528110216/http://www.savarbalistik.com.tr/content.php?icerikpk=22|archive-date=28 May 2014|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>|| [[File:Soldier Plate Carrier System (SPCS).jpg|150px]] || {{TUR}} || [[Ballistic vest]] || Standard issue in combat zones and on duty personnel. With varying versions.\n|}\n\n== Vehicles ==\n\n===Tanks===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- \n!style=\"width:7%;\"|Model!!Image!!style=\"width:10%;\"|Origin!!Type!!style=\"width:7%;\"|Variant!!Number!!Details\n|- valign=\"top\"\n| [[Altay (tank)|Altay]] || [[File:TankAltayT1_(1).jpg|170px]] || {{TUR}} || [[Main battle tank]] || || 10<ref name=\"worldbulletin\">{{cite web|url=http://www.worldbulletin.net/?aType=haber&ArticleID=98699|title=Turkey introduces main battle tank Altay - Politics - Worldbulletin News|publisher=worldbulletin.net|accessdate=5 September 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150701065135/http://www.worldbulletin.net/?aType=haber&ArticleID=98699|archive-date=1 July 2015|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> || Serial production will start in 2023 with the first batch consisting of 250 units and estimated to cost $2B. Three more similar batches are expected to be ordered.<ref>{{cite news|title=Local tank production contract litmus test for Ko\u00e7's defense business|url=http://www.hurriyetdailynews.com/local-tank-production-contract-litmus-test-for-kocs-defense-business.aspx?PageID=238&NID=69950&NewsCatID=483|date=5 August 2014|accessdate=30 November 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151208125210/http://www.hurriyetdailynews.com/local-tank-production-contract-litmus-test-for-kocs-defense-business.aspx?PageID=238&NID=69950&NewsCatID=483|archive-date=8 December 2015|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>http://www.hurriyetdailynews.com/contract-signed-for-mass-production-of-turkish-battle-tank-138733</ref><ref>https://www.strategypage.com/htmw/htarm/articles/20190929.aspx</ref>\n|- valign=\"top\"\n| [[Leopard 2]] || [[File:Leopard 2 A4 Dresden.JPG|170px]] || {{FRG}} || Main Battle Tank || NG<br>[[Leopard 2A4|A4]]<hr>Total || 1<br>341<hr>342<ref name=armyrecog/><ref name=globalsecurity/> || Bought from the German [[Bundeswehr]] in 2005.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.army-technology.com/projects/leopard/|title=Leopard 2 Main Battle Tank, Germany|publisher=army-technology.com|accessdate=30 November 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151117040254/http://www.army-technology.com/projects/leopard/|archive-date=17 November 2015|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://defence-blog.com/army/photo-of-upgrade-leopard-2ng-by-by-aselsan-of-turkey.html|title=Photo of upgrade Leopard 2NG by Aselsan of Turkey - Defence Blog|website=defence-blog.com|accessdate=30 December 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151229185904/http://defence-blog.com/army/photo-of-upgrade-leopard-2ng-by-by-aselsan-of-turkey.html|archive-date=29 December 2015|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> All modernized by [[ASELSAN]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hurriyet.com.tr/aselsan-leopard-2a4-tanki-modernizasyonunu-gerceklestirdi-ve-adini-leopard-2-next-generation-koydu-17720975|title=ASELSAN, Leopard 2A7 tank\u0131 modernizasyonunu ger\u00e7ekle\u015ftirdi ve ad\u0131n\u0131 \"Leopard 2 Next Generation\" koydu.|accessdate=24 June 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160701144332/http://www.hurriyet.com.tr/aselsan-leopard-2a4-tanki-modernizasyonunu-gerceklestirdi-ve-adini-leopard-2-next-generation-koydu-17720975|archive-date=1 July 2016|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n|- valign=\"top\"\n| [[Leopard 1]] || [[File:Brazilian Leopard 1 tank.jpg|170px]] || {{FRG}} || Main Battle Tank || [[Leopard 1#Turkey|1T]]<br>[[Leopard 1A3|A3]]<hr>Total || 170<ref name=\"sabah\">{{cite web|url=http://www.sabah.com.tr/ekonomi/2009/11/13/aselsanin_volkan_sistemi_ile_leopardlar_ilk_atista_vuracak|title=Aselsan'\u0131n Volkan sistemi ile Leopard'lar ilk at\u0131\u015fta vuracak - Ekonomi Haberleri|publisher=sabah.com.tr|accessdate=5 September 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924135510/http://www.sabah.com.tr/ekonomi/2009/11/13/aselsanin_volkan_sistemi_ile_leopardlar_ilk_atista_vuracak|archive-date=24 September 2015|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref><br>227<hr>397<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.militaryperiscope.com/mdb-smpl/weapons/gcv/tanks/w0000999.shtml|title=Leopard 1 main battle tank|publisher=Militaryperiscope.com|accessdate=18 December 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304045427/https://www.militaryperiscope.com/mdb-smpl/weapons/gcv/tanks/w0000999.shtml|archive-date=4 March 2016|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref> || Under an agreement signed in Bonn in November 1980, Turkey would obtain a first batch of 77 tanks by 1983. A further 150 were delivered by the end of 1991, and the last units were received by the end of 1994.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tanknutdave.com/the-german-leopard-1-series/|title=The German Leopard 1 Tank|publisher=TankNutDave.com|accessdate=24 December 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151225101721/http://tanknutdave.com/the-german-leopard-1-series/|archive-date=25 December 2015|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> In 2002 Turkey reached an agreement with [[ASELSAN]] Corporation to upgrade the Leopard 1 tanks, prolonging their service life by another 20 years.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.internethaber.com/tsk-leopard-1-tanki-ile-vuracak-215319h.htm|title=TSK Leopard-1 tank\u0131 ile vuracak|publisher=Internethaber.com|language=Turkish|accessdate=26 December 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304105909/http://www.internethaber.com/tsk-leopard-1-tanki-ile-vuracak-215319h.htm|archive-date=4 March 2016|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> This modernization ended suddenly in 2009 as a result of the [[Financial crisis of 2007\u201308|Financial crisis of 2008]] and only 170 out of the 397 units were modernized.<ref name=\"sabah\" />\n|- valign=\"top\"\n| [[M60 Patton]] || [[File:TankM60TM.jpg|170x170px]]\n|{{USA}}<br>{{ISR}} || Main Battle Tank ||[[Sabra (tank)|Sabra]]<br>TM<br>[[M60A3 TTS|A3 TTS]]<hr>Total\n|| 170 752<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.globalsecurity.org/military/world/europe/tu-army.htm|title=Turkish Land Forces - Kara Kuvvetleri Komutan|website=www.globalsecurity.org|accessdate=2020-02-09}}</ref><br>610<ref name=\"IISS2013\" /><br /><hr>1532<ref name=\"globalsecurity\" /><br>\n|| Obtained through Conventional Forces in Europe Treaty. Some upgraded to 'Sabra' by [[Israeli Military Industries]]. Contract was signed on March 29, 2002, estimated to be worth $688 million [[USD]].<ref name=gelbart>{{cite book|title=Modern Israeli Tanks and Infantry Carriers 1985-2004|publisher=[[Osprey Publishing]]|first=Marsh |last=Gelbart|year=2004|isbn=1-84176-579-1|page=29|url=https://books.google.com/?id=ldRRP_UnIjgC&pg=PA29&lpg=PA29&dq=Magach+7+Sabra#v=onepage&q=Magach%207%20Sabra&f=false}}</ref> \n\nM60TM<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.israeldefense.co.il/en/node/33566|title=Turkey Plans to Modernize its M60 MBTs {{!}} Israel Defense|website=www.israeldefense.co.il|language=en|accessdate=2019-11-05}}</ref> modernization started after the lessons learned from the [[Operation Euphrates Shield]]. [[M60A3]] tanks started to be equipped with new [[ASELSAN]] systems since 2017. SARP <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.aselsan.com.tr/en/capabilities/weapon-systems/remote-weapon-platforms/sarp-stabilized-advanced-remote-weapon-platform|title=SARP Stabilized Advanced Remote Weapon Platform {{!}} ASELSAN|website=www.aselsan.com.tr|accessdate=2019-11-05}}</ref>UKSS 12.7mm [[Remote control|remote control weapon systems]], YAMGOZ<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://en.azeridefence.com/yamgoz-close-range-surveillance-system/|title=YAMG\u00d6Z Close-Range Surveillance System|date=2017-04-14|website=Azeridefence|language=az|accessdate=2019-11-05}}</ref> [[360\u00b0]] close range surveillance system,TLUS<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.aselsan.com.tr/tr/cozumlerimiz/elektro-optik-sistemler/ana-muharebe-tanki-ve-zirhli-arac-gorus-sistemleri/tlus-tank-lazer-uyari-sistemi|title=TLUS - Tank Lazer Uyar\u0131 Sistemi {{!}} ASELSAN|website=www.aselsan.com.tr|accessdate=2019-11-05}}</ref> Laser warning system, AD\u0130S <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.aselsan.com.tr/en/capabilities/electro-optic-systems/main-battle-tank-and-infantry-fighting-vehicle-sighting-applications/adis-aselsan-drivers-vision-system|title=ADIS - ASELSAN DRIVER'S VISION SYSTEM {{!}} ASELSAN|website=www.aselsan.com.tr|accessdate=2019-11-05}}</ref>tank driver vision system, [[Reactive armour|ERA]] additional [[armor plates]], AKKOR PULAT<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.monch.com/mpg/news/land/5371-alta-aps.html|title=IDEF 2019: Aselsan AKKOR Active Protection Systems for ALTAY|website=www.monch.com|accessdate=2019-11-05}}</ref> 360\u00b0 active protection system,additional internal protection coating,new [[fire suppression system]],audible warning system, behind turret [[cage armor]] and 76mm smoke grenade launchers.\n|- valign=\"top\"\n| [[M48 Patton]] || [[File:M-48A5E2 Ej\u00e9rcito Espa\u00f1ol.JPG|170px]] || {{USA}} || Main Battle Tank ||[[M48A5T2|A5T2]]||758<ref name=\"IISS2013\">[[International Institute for Strategic Studies]]: The Military Balance 2013, p.183</ref>\n| The M48 was by far the most fielded tank of the [[Turkish Armed Forces]] with 3,008 units active during the Cold War, with the runner-up being the [[M47 Patton]] of which Turkey fielded 1,347.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.militaryfactory.com/armor/detail-page-2.asp?armor_id=33|title=M47 (Patton II) Medium Tank (1951)|publisher=Militaryfactory.com|accessdate=1 January 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160222122417/http://www.militaryfactory.com/armor/detail-page-2.asp?armor_id=33|archive-date=22 February 2016|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> All modernized.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.aksam.com.tr/foto-galeri/guncel/tanklar-burada-hayat-buluyor/16529/2|title=Foto Galeri - G\u00fcncel Haber Foto\u011fraflar\u0131 - Ak\u015fam|accessdate=24 June 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160823032306/http://www.aksam.com.tr/foto-galeri/guncel/tanklar-burada-hayat-buluyor/16529/2|archive-date=23 August 2016|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n*M48A5T1: Turkish M48 variant upgraded along similar lines to the M60A1, with an M68 105 mm main gun, passive night vision, M60A1 fire control system and an AVDS-1790 diesel engine. Used mainly for supporting ground forces. 400 in storage.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://askeriharekat.com/tsk-envanterinde-bulunan-tanklar/|title=TSK Envanterinde Bulunan Tanklar|date=2017-12-23|website=Askeri Harekat|language=tr|accessdate=2019-12-27}}</ref> \n*M48A5T2: Improved version of the M48A5T1 upgraded along similar lines to the M60A3 with thermal imaging, M60A3 fire control system and a laser rangefinder.\n|}\n\n===Armored vehicles===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- \n!style=\"width:7%;\"|Model!!Image!!style=\"width:9%;\"|Origin!!Type!!style=\"width:6%;\"|Variant!!Number!!Details\n|- valign=\"top\"\n| [[FNSS ACV-15]] ||[[File:Turkish ACV-300 in Mogadishu.jpg|190x190px]]||{{TUR}}||[[Infantry Fighting Vehicle|IFV]]<br>[[Armored Personnel Carrier|APC]]<br>[[Tank Destroyer|TD]]<br>[[Mortar carrier|MC]] || [[ACV-300|ACV-AIFV]]<br>[[ACV-300|ACV-AAPC]]<br>[[ACV-300|ACV-ATV]]<br>[[ACV-300|ACV-AMV]]<hr>Total || 650<br>1,400<br>50<br>180<hr>2,280<ref name=\"savunmasanayist.com\">{{cite web |title=T\u00fcrkiye \u2013 Yunanistan Kara Kuvvetleri kar\u015f\u0131la\u015ft\u0131rmas\u0131 |url=https://www.savunmasanayist.com/yunanistan-kara-kuvvetleri-karsilastirmasi/ |website=savunmasanayist.com |accessdate=27 March 2020}}</ref> || ACV-15 is license built variant of 