6x6-komando/|title=FNSS'ten \u00d6zel Kuvvetler'e \u00f6zel z\u0131rhl\u0131: PARS 6x6 KOMANDO|last=\u015eAH\u0130N|first=ANIL|date=2020-01-10|website=SavunmaSanayiST|language=Turkish|accessdate=2020-01-12}}</ref>||[[Special Forces Command (Turkey)|Special Forces Command]] will receive 12 PARS 6x6 KOMANDO variant, equipped with two remote controlled weapon stations and electronic countermeasure systems. It will enter inventory starting 2020.\n|- valign=\"top\"\n|[[FNSS Pars|FNSS PARS 8X8]]||[[File:ParsIII8x8 (1).jpg|170px]]||{{TUR}}||[[Armored Personnel Carrier]]|| [[Reconnaissance vehicle|Scout]]<br>[[CBRN defense|CBRN]]<br>[[Infantry fighting vehicle|IFV]]<hr>Total || 45<br>5<br>5<hr>55 ordered<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fnss.com.tr/en/news/pars-scout-8x8-and-6x6-enter-the-turkish-armed-forces-inventory |url-status=live |title=PARS SCOUT 8x8 and 6x6 Enter the Turkish Armed Forces\u2019 Inventory |accessdate=2020-03-27}}</ref>||\n|- valign=\"top\"\n|[[BTR-80]]||[[File:2011 Moscow Victory Day Parade (360-06) (cropped).jpg|170px]]||{{GDR}}<br>{{USSR}}||[[Armoured personnel carrier|Armored Personnel Carrier]]|| BTR-80M || 180<ref name=\"globalsecurity\" />|| Bought 110 from ex-[[GDR]] and 70 from ex-[[USSR]] stockpile between 1993 and 1999.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mdb.cast.ru/mdb/2-2001/at/raegct/|title=data|website=Moscow Defense Brief|accessdate=30 November 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151208093807/http://mdb.cast.ru/mdb/2-2001/at/raegct/|archive-date=8 December 2015|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>https://books.google.com.tr/books?id=b99dfVMJNRMC&pg=PA35&lpg=PA35&dq=turkey+btr+gdr&source=bl&ots=8QBt6KzLk-&sig=ACfU3U2AAVdEifdGnliv2ttcGbLUiYBG6A&hl=tr&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwirv8H4rbToAhVQWRUIHRBRBtwQ6AEwAHoECAoQAQ#v=onepage&q=turkey%20btr%20gdr&f=false</ref> All are modernized with thermal sight, new engine and electronics including climate contol. In storage.\n|- valign=\"top\"\n|[[BMC Kirpi]]||[[File:2012 Eurosatory BMC trucks.JPG|170px]]\n[