-weapon-platform|title=SARP Stabilized Advanced Remote Weapon Platform {{!}} ASELSAN|website=www.aselsan.com.tr|accessdate=2020-01-18}}</ref>\n\nStarting mid-2020, various Kirpi II's will be integrated with 20kW high power laser defense system (YGLS).<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.millisavunma.com/yuksek-guclu-lazer-sistemi-ygls-projesi/|title=Y\u00fcksek G\u00fc\u00e7l\u00fc Lazer Sistemi (YGLS) Projesi|last=millisavunma|date=2016-09-09|website=Millisavunma.com|language=tr|accessdate=2020-01-26}}</ref> Aselsan Armol laser defense system will be also integrated to various armored tactic vehicles such as BMC Kirpi, Otokar Cobra. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.defenceturk.net/tsk-envanterine-katilan-lazer-silahi-armol|title=TSK envanterine kat\u0131lan lazer silah\u0131: ARMOL|last=Alemdar|first=Ahmet|date=2019-09-30|website=DefenceTurk|language=tr|accessdate=2020-01-26}}</ref> With [[CBRN]] capabilities.\n|-\n|[[BMC Vuran]]\n|[http://www.armyrecognition.com/images/stories/europe/france/exhibition/eurosatory_2016/news/BMC_Vehicles_640_002.jpg]\n|{{TUR}}\n|[[Mine-Resistant Ambush Protected|MRAP]]<br>\n|Vuran 4X4<br>Vuran ALKAR [[Mortar carrier|MC]]<hr>Total\n|230<ref>https://www.trmilitarynews.com/bmc-vuran-teslimati-tam-gaz-suruyor/</ref><br>80+<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.janes.com/article/88252/idef-2019-alkar-120-mm-mortar-enters-turkish-service|title=IDEF 2019: Alkar 120 mm mortar enters Turkish service {{!}} Jane's 360|website=www.janes.com|accessdate=2019-11-05}}</ref><hr>300+\n|\n|- valign=\"top\"\n|[[Otokar Cobra]]||[[File:Paradbaku98.jpg|170px]]<br>[[File:OtokarCobraII.jpg|170px]]\n|{{TUR}}||[[Infantry mobility vehicle]]||Cobra<br>Cobra II<hr>Total\n| 1200+<ref name=\"savunmasanayist.com\"/><br>300<ref name=\"savunmasanayist.com\"/><hr>1500+\n| Variants such as forward observation vehicle, armoured ambulance, armoured command post, 20 mm autocannon and ground surveillance radar vehicle are in use. In late 2015, the Turkish Armed Forces ordered 82 Cobra II vehicles plus related systems, maintenance and support worth $52 million. In June 2016, the Turkish Armed Forces ordered an undisclosed number of Cobra II vehicles plus related systems, maintenance and support worth $120.8 million. Assuming the same value to vehicle ratio as the 2015 order, this would imply an order of about 180 vehicles.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.defenceturkey.com/tr/icerik/a-look-at-the-turkish-defense-industry-land-platforms-systems-sector-3027|title=A Look at the Turkish Defense Industry Land Platforms/Systems Sector - Defence Turkey Magazine|website=www.defenceturkey.com|accessdate=2019-11-05}}</ref> With [[CBRN]] capabilities.\n|-\n|[[Otokar Akrep]]||[[File:Mosul, Iraq.jpg|170px]]\n|{{TUR}}||[[Infantry mobility vehicle]]||Akrep I\n| 550+<ref name=\"savunmasanayist.com\"/>\n| Variants such as forward observation vehicle, armoured ambulance, remote turret and ground surveillance radar vehicle are in use. \n|- valign=\"top\"\n| [[Nurol Ejder]]||[[File:Ejder.jpg|170px]]||{{TUR}}||[[Infantry mobility vehicle]]||Yal\u00e7\u0131n 4x4||300+<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.teknolojioku.com/haber/tskdan-mayina-rokete-bombaya-dayanikli-ejder-yalcin-4x4-hamlesi-30542.html|title=TSK'dan may\u0131na, rokete, bombaya dayan\u0131kl\u0131 Ejder Yal\u00e7\u0131n 4x4 hamlesi!|last=Teknolojioku|date=14 September 2015|website=Teknolojioku|accessdate=24 April 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160314162548/http://www.teknolojioku.com/haber/tskdan-mayina-rokete-bombaya-dayanikli-ejder-yalcin-4x4-hamlesi-30542.html|archive-date=14 March 2016|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>|| \n|-\n|[[FNSS Defence Systems|FNSS Kaplan]]\n|[[File:KaplanSTA.jpg|frameless|150x150px]]\n|{{TUR}}\n|[[Tank Destroyer]]\n|Kaplan TD\n|6 \n|FNSS Kaplan will be equipped with remote controlled ATGM turret. 184 vehicles were ordered.<ref name=\"FNSS to deliver PARS and Kaplan\" />\n|-\n|FNSS PARS\n|[[File:Pars4x4AntiTank.jpg|frameless|150x150px]]\n|{{TUR}}\n|[[Tank Destroyer]]\n| 