}} || [[Short-range ballistic missile|SRBM]] || || 20 || Similar to the Chinese [[B-611]]. 100 missiles in stock.<ref name=armyrecog/> They are launched from the German [[MAN SE|MAN 26.372]]<ref name=armyrecog/> trucks.\n|- valign=\"top\"\n| [[MGM-140 ATACMS]] || [[File:ATACMSMay2006.jpg|170px]] || {{USA}} || [[Short-range ballistic missile|SRBM]] || Block 1A<ref>https://web.archive.org/web/20160108172744/http://www.deagel.com/search.aspx?key=atacms</ref> || 72 || with 120 missiles in stock.<ref name=\"fas\">{{cite web|url=https://fas.org/spp/starwars/congress/1995/s951211a.htm|title=Sale of ATACMS Ballistic Missiles to Turkey|publisher=fas.org|accessdate=5 September 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150409033402/https://fas.org/spp/starwars/congress/1995/s951211a.htm|archive-date=9 April 2015|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"missilethreat\">{{cite web|url=http://missilethreat.com/missiles/mgm-140-164-168-atacms/|title=MGM-140/-164/-168 ATACMS - Missile ThreatM39 - Missile Threat|publisher=missilethreat.com|accessdate=5 September 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151010205355/http://missilethreat.com/missiles/mgm-140-164-168-atacms/|archive-date=10 October 2015|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n|- valign=\"top\"\n| [[M270]] || [[File:MARS (MLRS) Bundeswehr.jpg|170px]] || {{USA}}|| [[Multiple Rocket Launcher|MRL]] || M270A1 || 12<ref name=armyrecog/> || In 1992 Turkey purchased 12 units from US. Later during the mid 90s further 24 units were requested but under the condition that they and the rockets were to be produced in Turkey. US refused and no further acquisition followed.<ref name=\"MLRS\">{{cite web|url=http://www.acig.info/CMS/?option=com_content&task=view&id=191&Itemid=47|title=Turkish Surface to Surface Rocket and Missile Systems - II|publisher=ACIG.org|accessdate=2 December 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151208041602/http://www.acig.info/CMS/?option=com_content&task=view&id=191&Itemid=47|archive-date