013/ |archivedate=25 December 2016 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> || \n|- valign=\"top\"\n| [[HEMTT]] || [[File:HEMTT Wrecker and Cargo.jpg|170px]] || {{USA}} || Very Heavy Truck<br>(12,000&nbsp;kg) || 80<ref name=\"weebly\" /><ref name=\"Jane's Logistics, Support & Unmanned 2015-2016 Oshkosh M977 Heavy Expanded Mobility Tactical Truck (HEMTT) and M989A1 Heavy Expanded Mobility Ammunition Trailer (HEMAT)\">{{cite web |url=https://janes.ihs.com/CustomPages/Janes/DisplayPage.aspx?DocType=Reference&ItemId=+++1495090&Pubabbrev=JLSU |title=Oshkosh M977 heavy expanded mobility tactical truck (HEMTT) and M989A1 heavy expanded mobility ammunition trailer (HEMAT) |publisher=IHS Jane's Shaun C Connors & Christopher F Foss |date=2015-06-14 |accessdate=2015-06-14}}</ref> || \n|- valign=\"top\"\n| [[MAN LX and FX ranges of tactical trucks|MAN LX and FX]] || [[File:MAN LX Lux.jpg|170px]] || {{GER}} || Heavy Truck<br>(5-10,000&nbsp;kg) || x<ref name=\"Jane's Logistics, Support & Unmanned 2015-2016 (MAN/RMMV FX, LX and SX ranges of tactical trucks)\">{{cite web |url=https://janes.ihs.com/CustomPages/Janes/DisplayPage.aspx?DocType=Reference&ItemId=+++1494996&Pubabbrev=JLSU|title=MAN/RMMV FX, LX and SX ranges of tactical trucks|publisher=IHS Jane's|date=2015-05-27 |accessdate=2015-08-25}}</ref> || \n|- valign=\"top\"\n| [[BMC (Turkey)|BMC 380-26]] || [https://www.bmc.com.tr/en/defense-industry/tactical-wheeled-vehicle] || {{TUR}} || Heavy Truck<br>(10,000&nbsp;kg) || 403<ref name=armyrecog/> || \n|- valign=\"top\"\n| [[BMC (Turkey)|BMC 235-16]] || [https://www.bmc.com.tr/en/defense-industry/tactical-wheeled-vehicle] || {{TUR}} || Heavy Truck<br>(5,000&nbsp;kg) || 282<ref name=armyrecog/> || \n|- valign=\"top\"\n| [[BMC (Turkey)|BMC 185-09]] || [https://www.bmc.com.tr/en/defense-industry/tactical-wheeled-vehicle] || {{TUR}} || Medium Truck<br>(2,500&nbsp;kg) || 706<ref name=armyrecog/> ||Also known as BMC EFE<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ssb.gov.tr/urunkatalog/en/36/|title=TURKISH DEFENCE INDUSTRY PRODUCT CATALOGUE|website=www.ssb.gov.tr|accessdate=2020-01-19}}</ref>\n|- valign=\"top\"\n| [[Unimog|Mercedes Unimog]] || [[File:Mercedes-Benz Unimog U 5000.jpg|170px]] || {{FRG}}<br>{{TUR}} || Medium Truck<br>(2,500&nbsp;kg) || 5,500<ref name=jamesron/><ref name=militaryfactory3>{{cite web|title=Unimog|url=http://www.militaryfactory.com/armor/detail.asp?armor_id=651|website=Military Factory|accessdate=4 June 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140606232832/http://www.militaryfactory.com/armor/detail.asp?armor_id=651|archive-date=6 June 2014|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> || Produced by Mercedes-Benz T\u00fcrk.\n|- valign=\"top\"\n| [[Mercedes-Benz Actros]] || [[File:Actros 3344 Ej\u00e9rcito.JPG|170px]] || {{GER}}<br>{{TUR}} || Truck Tractor || 380<ref name=\"weebly\">{{cite web|title=Turkish Army Inventory|url=http://turk-ordusu.weebly.com/tuumlrk-kara-ordusu-envanteri.html|website=turk-ordusu.weebly.com|accessdate=14 May 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160616182650/http://turk-ordusu.weebly.com/tuumlrk-kara-ordusu-envanteri.html|archive-date=16 June 2016|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> || Produced by Mercedes-Benz T\u00fcrk.\n|- valign=\"top\"\n| [[Mercedes Axor]] || [[File:Mercedes Benz Axor 1829 A 4x4 Bundeswehr.jpg|170px]] || {{GER}}<br>{{TUR}} || Truck Tractor || 140<ref name=\"weebly\" /> || Produced by Mercedes-Benz T\u00fcrk.\n|- valign=\"top\"\n| [[BMC (Turkey)|BMC TU\u011eRA]] || [https://i2.wp.com/www.defenceturk.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/BMC-Tu%C4%9Fra-tank-ta%C5%9F%C4%B1y%C4%B1c%C4%B1.jpg?fit=750%2C422&ssl=1] || {{TUR}} || Truck Tractor || 72<ref>https://www.defenceturk.net/tskya-72-adetlik-8x8-tugra-tank-tasiyici-arac-teslimati</ref> || \n|- valign=\"top\"\n| [[BMC (Turkey)|BMC AKTAN]] || [https://www.bmc.com.tr/en/defense-industry/logistic-support-vehicles/technical] ||{{TUR}} || Fuel Tanker || x<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bmc.com.tr/static/lojistik_destek/aktan/technical.jpg |url-status=live |title=Fuel Tanker |accessdate=2020-03-27}}</ref> || AKTAN can carry 12,000 litres of fuel. The vehicle can both pump the fuel in its tank into the recipient air platform, and can also pump fuel out of a tank on another vehicle and pump it to a different point. The vehicle is capable of refuelling up to four aircraft, either simultaneously or separately.\nThe tank has been designed on an incline to fully transfer the fuel when necessary, and contains baffles to prevent sloshing while on the move. The tank body is made of aluminium alloy and is coated with a ballistic sealing material and fire-retardant paint. Designed in compliance with the railway loading gauge, the size of the vehicle permits its transportation aboard an [[Airbus A400M Atlas|A400M cargo aircraft]].\n<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.milscint.com/en/bmc-unveils-aktan/|title=BMC Unveils AKTAN \u2013 MSI Turkish Defence Review / MSI TDR Reference Magazine of Turkish Defence and Aviation Industry|website=www.milscint.com|language=tr-TR|accessdate=2020-01-24}}</ref>\n|-\n|}\n\n=== Unmanned ground vehicles ===\n<br />\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Model\n!Image\n!Origin\n!Type\n!Number\n!Details\n|-\n|UKAP\n|[[File:ASELSAN 0-\u0130KA 2 \u0130nsans\u0131z Kara Arac\u0131, Teknofest 2019.jpg|227x227px]]\n|{{TUR}}\n\n|[[Unmanned ground vehicle]]\n|25+ ordered\n|Weapon Platform (UKAP), developed by defense contractors Katmerciler and [[ASELSAN]].\n<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.defenseworld.net/news/22380/Turkey___s_New_Armed_Unmanned_Armed_Vehicle____UKAP____To_Be_Exported_To_Asian_Region#.XcE7gpr0mUk|title=Turkey's New Armed Unmanned Armed Vehicle 'UKAP' To Be Exported To Asian Region|website=www.defenseworld.net|accessdate=2019-11-05}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://thedefensepost.com/2018/02/22/turkey-armed-unmanned-ground-vehicles-afrin-syria/|title=Turkey says armed unmanned ground vehicles to be used in Afrin|date=2018-02-22|website=The Defense Post|language=en-US|accessdate=2019-11-05}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=