00<ref name=\"hurriyetdailynews.com\">{{cite web|url=http://www.hurriyetdailynews.com/default.aspx?pageid=438&n=defense-panel-may-select-new-copter-type-tuesday-2011-03-21|title=ECONOMY - Turkish defense panel may select new copter type Tuesday|publisher=hurriyetdailynews.com|accessdate=5 September 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924045856/http://www.hurriyetdailynews.com/default.aspx?pageid=438&n=defense-panel-may-select-new-copter-type-tuesday-2011-03-21|archive-date=24 September 2015|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> ||A version of [[AgustaWestland AW149]] named TUHP149, and the Turkish T-70 version of the [[Sikorsky S-70|S-70i Black Hawk]], were candidates for the programme which worth $4&nbsp;billion.<ref name=\"hurriyetdailynews.com\"/> On 21 April 2011 the Turkish defence minister announced that the Sikorsky T-70 Black Hawk had been declared the winner.<ref name=\"flightglobal2\">{{cite web|url=http://www.flightglobal.com/news/articles/sikorsky-wins-turkish-utility-helicopter-battle-355885/|title=Sikorsky wins Turkish utility helicopter battle|publisher=flightglobal.com|accessdate=5 September 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150721062033/http://www.flightglobal.com/news/articles/sikorsky-wins-turkish-utility-helicopter-battle-355885/|archive-date=21 July 2015|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n|-\n| Indigenous Helicopter Project|| [[Utility helicopter]] || TBD || Under Development by TAI.<ref name=\"globalsecurity3\">{{cite web|url=http://www.globalsecurity.org/military/world/europe/tu-tihp.htm|title=Turkish Indigenous Helicopter Program|author=John Pike|publisher=globalsecurity.org|accessdate=5 September 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924144059/http://www.globalsecurity.org/military/world/europe/tu-tihp.htm|archive-date=24 September 2015|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"trdefence\">{{cite web|url=http://www.trdefence.com/?p=1411|title=STM Prepared Feasibility Report for Turkish Indigenous Helicopter - TR Defence|publisher=trdefence.com|accessdate=5 September 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| Next Gen APC || [[Armored Personnel Carrier]] || TBD ||A competition exists between Turkeys two largest arms producers in winning the contract to supply Turkey's next generation APC which is intended to replace all of the BTR-80 and M113s. The [[FNSS Defence Systems]] is offering the [[FNSS Pars|Pars]]<ref name=globalsecurity/> while the [[Otokar|Otokar Corporation]] is offering the [[Otokar Arma|Arma]].<ref name=globalsecurity/> The results of the competitions will be announced in 2016, however, Azerbaijan has already demonstrated interest in the Arma which may sway the final ruling in Otokar's favor.\n|-\n| Special Purpose Tactical Wheeled Armored Vehicles Procurement Project || [[CBRN]] [[armored vehicle]] || 428 || Procurement of Special Purpose Tactical Wheeled Armored Vehicles and related mission equipment for tactical reconnaissance, surveillance and CBRN (Chemical, Biological, Radiological and Nuclear) reconnaissance missions of Turkish Land Forces.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ssm.gov.tr/home/projects/Sayfalar/proje.aspx?projeID=282 |title=HATA |publisher=SSM |accessdate=2018-07-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160603171541/http://www.ssm.gov.tr/home/projects/Sayfalar/proje.aspx?projeID=282 |archive-date=3 June 2016 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n|-\n| Low-level Airborne Ground Surveillance Zeppelin Project || [[Airborne ground surveillance]] [[zeppelin]] || TBD || Probably the [[Tethered Aerostat Radar System]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hurriyet.com.tr/sinira-zeplin-21768215|title=S\u0131n\u0131ra zeplin|accessdate=17 January 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160928133245/http://www.hurriyet.com.tr/sinira-zeplin-21768215|archive-date=28 September 2016|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> To meet the \"low-level border surveillance\" requirement of Turkish Land Forces Command.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hurriyet.com.tr/isid-e-karsi-zeplin-gozu-29618489?_sgm_campaign=scn_a004ff5fd97f8006&_sgm_source=29618489&_sgm_action=click|title=I\u015e\u0130D'e kar\u015f\u0131 \"Zeplin\" g\u00f6z\u00fc|accessdate=17 January 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160513005039/http://www.hurriyet.com.tr/isid-e-karsi-zeplin-gozu-29618489?_sgm_campaign=scn_a004ff5fd97f8006&_sgm_source=29618489&_sgm_action=click|archive-date=13 May 2016|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n|-\n| Man Portable Fire and Forget Short Range Anti-Tank Weapon Project || [[Anti-tank missile]] || TBD || Delivery of man portable fire and forget short range anti-tank weapon.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ssm.gov.tr/home/projects/Sayfalar/proje.aspx?projeID=290 |title=HATA |publisher=SSM |accessdate=2018-07-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160603161156/http://www.ssm.gov.tr/home/projects/Sayfalar/proje.aspx?projeID=290 |archive-date=3 June 2016 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n|-\n| Mine Cleaning System Project || [[Demining]] equipment || 50 || Fast breaching of the minefield in the combat field to create a safe path for troops.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ssm.gov.tr/home/projects/Sayfalar/proje.aspx?projeID=121 |title=HATA |publisher=SSM |accessdate=2018-07-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160603171826/http://www.ssm.gov.tr/home/projects/Sayfalar/proje.aspx?projeID=121 |archive-date=3 June 2016 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n|-\n| Multispectral Camouflage System Project || [[Multi-spectral camouflage]] || TBD || Multispectral camouflage net and mobile multispectral camouflage systems will be indigenously developed in order to increase the hiding capabilities of troops in the field and weapons/systems/tactical vehicles.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ssm.gov.tr/home/projects/Sayfalar/proje.aspx?projeID=353 |title=HATA |publisher=SSM |accessdate=2018-07-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160603172742/http://www.ssm.gov.tr/home/projects/Sayfalar/proje.aspx?projeID=353 |archive-date=3 June 2016 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n|-\n| Flexible Layer Cage Armour System Project || [[Cage armor]] || TBD || Flexible layer cage armour system will be indigenously developed in order to increase the survivability capability of tanks and armoured vehicles against anti-tank rockets.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ssm.gov.tr/home/projects/Sayfalar/proje.aspx?projeID=352 |title=HATA |publisher=SSM |accessdate=2018-07-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160603170007/http://www.ssm.gov.tr/home/projects/Sayfalar/proje.aspx?projeID=352 |archive-date=3 June 2016 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all}}</ref> \n|}\n\n==See also==\n* [[Military equipment of Turkey]]\n* [[List of modern weapons of the Turkish Air Force]]\n* [[Turkish Naval Forces#Equipment|Equipment of the Turkish Naval Forces]]\n* [[Turkish Gendarmerie#Equipment|Equipment of the Turkish Gendarmerie]]\n* [[Turkish Coast Guard#Equipment|Equipment of the Turkish Coast Guard]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*See the [https://web.archive.org/web/20080528040418/http://www.ssm.gov.tr/EN/Projeler/Pages/default.aspx Turkish Government, Undersecretariat for Defense Industries] website for an official list of Turkish military procurement projects.\n\n{{Turkish Army equipment}}\n{{Military ranks by country}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Modern Equipment And Uniform Of The Turkish Army}}\n[[Category:Military equipment of Turkey]]\n[[Category:Turkish Army]]\n[[Category:Turkish military-related lists]]\n[[Category:Lists of military equipment|Turkish Land Forces]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2012}}\n{{Turkish Army}}\n'''Modern equipment of the [[Turkish Land Forces]]'''. Totals in these tables do not necessary accurately reflect combat attrition sustained during the ongoing [[2019 Syrian-Turkish clashes|Syrian-Turkish clashes]] and [[Kurdish\u2013Turkish conflict (1978\u2013present)|Kurdish\u2013Turkish conflict]].\n\n== Infantry weapons ==\n\n===Handguns===\n{| class=\"wikitabl