-ilki-yuzunu-gosterdi-gundem-2184527/|title=Chinook'lar\u0131n ilki y\u00fcz\u00fcn\u00fc g\u00f6sterdi - Son Dakika Haberler|accessdate=17 January 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161005143351/http://m.milliyet.com.tr/chinook-larin-ilki-yuzunu-gosterdi-gundem-2184527/|archive-date=5 October 2016|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>||[[File:CH-47 Chinook TurkishArmy Teknofest2019.jpg|147x147px]]||{{USA}} || [[Transport helicopter]] || 11 || CH-47F variant in use.\n|-\n|[[Sikorsky S-70|S-70 Black Hawk]]<ref name=flightglobal1/>|| [[File:US Navy 090708-N-5215E-078 Aviation Boatswain's Mate (handling) 3rd Class Mario Teasley directs a landing S-70 Black Hawk assigned to the Royal Australian Army during a Deck Landing Qualification.jpg|150px]] || {{USA}}<br>{{TUR}} || [[Utility helicopter]] || 57 || T-70 variant in use. 50+ more on order. Produced under license by [[Turkish Aerospace Industries|TAI]].\n|-\n|[[Sikorsky UH-60 Black Hawk|UH-60 Black Hawk]]<ref name=armyrecog/>|| [[File:Turkish ISAF UH-60 Black Hawk helicopter.JPEG|150px]] || {{USA}} || [[Utility helicopter]] || 86 || UH-60A variant in use. All modernized.\n|-\n|[[Eurocopter AS532 Cougar|AS532 Cougar]]<ref name=armyrecog/>|| [[File:AS-532 Cougar kzlsngr3.JPG|150px]] || {{FRA}} || [[Utility helicopter]] || 40 || AS532UL MkII variant in use. All modernized.\n|-\n|[[Bell UH-1 Iroquois|UH-1 Iroquois]]<ref name=armyrecog/><ref name=flightglobal/>|| [[File:\u0130stanbul 5402.jpg|150px]] || {{USA}} || [[Utility helicopter]] || 177 || UH-1H variant in use. Being replaced by T-70. All modernized.\n|-\n|[[Bell UH-1N Twin Huey|UH-1N Twin Huey]]<ref name=globalsecurity/>|| [[File:Agusta AB-212, Austria - Air Force AN0182336.jpg|150px]] || {{USA}}<br>{{ITA}} || [[Utility helicopter]] || 18 || AB 212 variant in use. Being replaced by T-70. All modernized.\n|-\n|[[Mil Mi-17|Mi-17]]<ref name=globalsecurity/>|| [[File:PLA Mil Mi-17-1 at Chelyabinsk Shagol Air Base.jpg|150px]] || {{USSR}} || [[Utility helicopter]